---
export const prerender = true;
import Layout from "../../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout
    title="The Story Behind the Name — MDRPedia, MDpedia & DRpedia"
    description="How MDRPedia became MDpedia in the West and DRpedia in the East. The origin story of one medical encyclopedia known by three names worldwide."
>
    <article class="name-story">
        <div class="container">
            <!-- Breadcrumb -->
            <nav class="story-breadcrumb" aria-label="Breadcrumb">
                <a href="/">MDRPedia</a> <span>/</span>
                <a href="/about">About</a> <span>/</span>
                <span aria-current="page">Our Name</span>
            </nav>

            <!-- Hero -->
            <header class="story-hero">
                <span class="story-eyebrow">Origins</span>
                <h1>One Register.<br><em>Three Names.</em></h1>
                <p class="story-lede">
                    How a medical encyclopedia born in Zurich became known as
                    MDpedia in Boston, DRpedia in Cairo, and MDRPedia everywhere in between.
                </p>
            </header>

            <!-- The Narrative -->
            <section class="story-body">
                <div class="drop-cap">
                    <p>
                        When MDRPedia launched its beta in 2022 with the "Titan 100" — the first hundred
                        physicians to meet its strictest verification criteria — the founding team chose
                        the name deliberately. <strong>MDR</strong> was shorthand for "Medical Doctor Register,"
                        and <strong>Pedia</strong> invoked the encyclopedic tradition of comprehensive, citable
                        knowledge. The full name, MDRPedia, was designed to be universal: a register that
                        belonged to no single country, credential, or culture.
                    </p>
                </div>

                <p>
                    But language has a will of its own. Within months of launch, two distinct shorthands
                    emerged — organically, independently, and along a line that traced a cultural divide
                    older than modern medicine itself.
                </p>

                <h2>The Western Shorthand: MDpedia</h2>
                <div class="name-callout west">
                    <div class="name-callout__name">MDpedia</div>
                    <div class="name-callout__origin">From "MD" — Medicinae Doctor</div>
                </div>
                <p>
                    In the United States, Canada, the United Kingdom, Germany, France, and Australia,
                    physicians began dropping the "R" and calling the platform simply <strong>MDpedia</strong>.
                    The reason was intuitive: in Western medical systems, the <strong>MD</strong> (Doctor of Medicine)
                    is the defining credential. Medical school graduates earn an MD. Hospitals hire MDs.
                    Journals publish MDs. The two letters are an identity.
                </p>
                <p>
                    When Western doctors saw "MDRPedia," their eyes naturally landed on "MD" — and "MDpedia"
                    rolled off the tongue in hallways, grand rounds, and conference bars. Academic journals
                    began citing the platform as "MDpedia" in footnotes. Residents texted each other to
                    "check MDpedia." The shorthand stuck.
                </p>

                <h2>The Eastern Shorthand: DRpedia</h2>
                <div class="name-callout east">
                    <div class="name-callout__name">DRpedia</div>
                    <div class="name-callout__origin">From "Dr." — the universal honorific</div>
                </div>
                <p>
                    Halfway across the world, a different abbreviation took hold. In India, Egypt, Saudi Arabia,
                    the UAE, China, Japan, Nigeria, Kenya, and across South-East Asia, the platform became known
                    as <strong>DRpedia</strong> — reading the "DR" in "MDR" and pairing it with "pedia."
                </p>
                <p>
                    The cultural logic was just as clear. In Eastern medical traditions, a physician is first
                    and foremost a <strong>Doctor</strong>. The specific degree — MBBS, MBChB, MD, or any
                    regional equivalent — matters less than the title itself. "Dr." is how patients address
                    their physicians, how physicians introduce themselves, and how communities honor their healers.
                    It carries a weight of social respect that transcends clinical specialization.
                </p>
                <p>
                    When physicians in these regions saw "MDRPedia," they read "DR" — and "DRpedia" became
                    the name whispered in hospital corridors from Mumbai to Nairobi, from Riyadh to Shanghai.
                </p>

                <h2>The Line on the Map</h2>
                <div class="map-section">
                    <div class="map-card">
                        <h4>MDpedia Regions</h4>
                        <ul>
                            <li>United States & Canada</li>
                            <li>United Kingdom & Ireland</li>
                            <li>Western & Central Europe</li>
                            <li>Australia & New Zealand</li>
                            <li>Scandinavia</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div class="map-divider">
                        <span>MDR</span>
                    </div>
                    <div class="map-card">
                        <h4>DRpedia Regions</h4>
                        <ul>
                            <li>Middle East & North Africa</li>
                            <li>India, Pakistan & South Asia</li>
                            <li>China, Japan & East Asia</li>
                            <li>Sub-Saharan Africa</li>
                            <li>South-East Asia</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <h2>Why We Kept All Three</h2>
                <p>
                    The founding team made a deliberate decision: do not fight the shorthands. Both names
                    reflect something true about the physicians who use the platform. An MD in Philadelphia
                    and a Dr. in Lahore are reading the same profiles, citing the same evidence, and trusting
                    the same verification — they simply arrive by a different door.
                </p>
                <p>
                    Today, the official name remains <strong>MDRPedia</strong>. But we recognize both
                    <a href="/about/mdpedia">MDpedia</a> and <a href="/about/drpedia">DRpedia</a> as
                    legitimate names for the same register. All three names appear in our structured data,
                    our press guidelines, and our brand system. Because a register that serves all physicians
                    should answer to whatever they call it.
                </p>

                <blockquote>
                    "The best name for an encyclopedia is the one its readers use."
                    <cite>— MDRPedia Editorial Board, 2024</cite>
                </blockquote>
            </section>

            <!-- Related Links -->
            <nav class="story-related">
                <h3>Continue Reading</h3>
                <div class="related-grid">
                    <a href="/about/mdpedia" class="related-card">
                        <span class="related-label">Western Name</span>
                        <strong>What is MDpedia?</strong>
                    </a>
                    <a href="/about/drpedia" class="related-card">
                        <span class="related-label">Eastern Name</span>
                        <strong>What is DRpedia?</strong>
                    </a>
                    <a href="/about" class="related-card">
                        <span class="related-label">Methodology</span>
                        <strong>About MDRPedia</strong>
                    </a>
                    <a href="/brand" class="related-card">
                        <span class="related-label">Design</span>
                        <strong>Brand System</strong>
                    </a>
                </div>
            </nav>
        </div>
    </article>

    <!-- Article Schema -->
    <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({
        "@context": "https://schema.org",
        "@type": "Article",
        "headline": "The Story Behind the Name: MDRPedia, MDpedia & DRpedia",
        "description": "How MDRPedia became MDpedia in the West and DRpedia in the East.",
        "author": { "@type": "Organization", "name": "MDRPedia" },
        "publisher": { "@type": "Organization", "name": "MDRPedia", "url": "https://mdrpedia.com" },
        "url": "https://mdrpedia.com/about/our-name",
        "datePublished": "2024-06-01",
        "dateModified": "2026-04-01",
        "about": [
            { "@type": "Thing", "name": "MDpedia" },
            { "@type": "Thing", "name": "DRpedia" },
            { "@type": "Thing", "name": "MDRPedia" }
        ]
    })} />

    <!-- BreadcrumbList Schema -->
    <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({
        "@context": "https://schema.org",
        "@type": "BreadcrumbList",
        "itemListElement": [
            { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 1, "name": "MDRPedia", "item": "https://mdrpedia.com" },
            { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 2, "name": "About", "item": "https://mdrpedia.com/about" },
            { "@type": "ListItem", "position": 3, "name": "Our Name", "item": "https://mdrpedia.com/about/our-name" }
        ]
    })} />
</Layout>

<style>
    .name-story { max-width: 780px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 0 20px 100px; }

    .story-breadcrumb {
        padding: 20px 0; font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 12px;
        color: var(--ink-3); letter-spacing: 0.04em;
    }
    .story-breadcrumb a { color: var(--ink-2); text-decoration: none; }
    .story-breadcrumb a:hover { text-decoration: underline; }
    .story-breadcrumb span { margin: 0 6px; }

    .story-eyebrow {
        display: inline-block; font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 10px;
        letter-spacing: 0.18em; text-transform: uppercase; color: var(--ink-3);
        margin-bottom: 16px;
    }

    .story-hero { padding: 40px 0 48px; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--rule); }
    .story-hero h1 {
        font-family: var(--font-serif); font-size: clamp(40px, 6vw, 64px);
        font-weight: 300; line-height: 1.05;
    }
    .story-hero h1 em { font-style: italic; color: var(--ink-3); font-weight: 300; }
    .story-lede {
        font-family: var(--font-serif); font-size: 20px; line-height: 1.5;
        color: var(--ink-2); margin-top: 20px; max-width: 52ch;
    }

    .story-body { padding-top: 48px; }
    .story-body h2 {
        font-family: var(--font-serif); font-size: 1.6rem; font-weight: 400;
        color: var(--ink); margin: 3rem 0 1rem; padding-top: 1.5rem;
        border-top: 1px solid var(--rule);
    }
    .story-body p {
        font-family: var(--font-serif); font-size: 18px; line-height: 1.7;
        color: var(--ink-2); margin-bottom: 1.2rem;
    }
    .story-body a { color: var(--ink-blue); text-decoration: underline; text-underline-offset: 2px; }

    .drop-cap p::first-letter {
        font-size: 68px; float: left; line-height: 0.82;
        padding: 6px 10px 0 0; font-weight: 300; color: var(--ink);
    }

    /* Name callouts */
    .name-callout {
        padding: 24px 28px; margin: 20px 0 24px;
        border-radius: var(--r-3); border-left: 4px solid var(--ink-blue);
        background: var(--paper-2);
    }
    .name-callout.east { border-left-color: var(--aged-gold); }
    .name-callout__name {
        font-family: var(--font-serif); font-size: 32px; font-weight: 400;
        line-height: 1; margin-bottom: 4px;
    }
    .name-callout__origin {
        font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 12px; color: var(--ink-3);
        letter-spacing: 0.08em;
    }

    /* Map section */
    .map-section {
        display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr auto 1fr; gap: 20px;
        margin: 24px 0 32px; align-items: stretch;
    }
    .map-card {
        padding: 24px; background: var(--paper-2); border: 1px solid var(--rule);
        border-radius: var(--r-3);
    }
    .map-card h4 {
        font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 11px; letter-spacing: 0.14em;
        text-transform: uppercase; color: var(--ink-3); margin-bottom: 12px;
    }
    .map-card ul { list-style: none; padding: 0; margin: 0; }
    .map-card li {
        padding: 6px 0; font-size: 14px; color: var(--ink-2);
        border-bottom: 1px solid var(--rule);
    }
    .map-card li:last-child { border-bottom: none; }
    .map-divider {
        display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center;
        writing-mode: vertical-rl; text-orientation: mixed;
        font-family: var(--font-serif); font-size: 24px; font-weight: 300;
        color: var(--ink-3); border-left: 1px dashed var(--rule);
        border-right: 1px dashed var(--rule); padding: 0 12px;
    }

    /* Blockquote */
    .story-body blockquote {
        margin: 2.5rem 0; padding: 24px 28px;
        border-left: 3px solid var(--ink); background: var(--paper-2);
        font-family: var(--font-serif); font-size: 20px; font-style: italic;
        color: var(--ink); line-height: 1.5;
    }
    .story-body blockquote cite {
        display: block; margin-top: 12px; font-size: 13px;
        font-style: normal; font-family: var(--font-mono);
        color: var(--ink-3); letter-spacing: 0.04em;
    }

    /* Related */
    .story-related {
        margin-top: 3rem; padding-top: 2rem; border-top: 2px solid var(--rule);
    }
    .story-related h3 {
        font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 11px; letter-spacing: 0.18em;
        text-transform: uppercase; color: var(--ink-3); margin-bottom: 16px;
    }
    .related-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; gap: 12px; }
    .related-card {
        padding: 20px; background: var(--paper-2); border: 1px solid var(--rule);
        border-radius: var(--r-3); text-decoration: none; color: var(--ink);
        transition: border-color var(--t-fast) var(--ease);
    }
    .related-card:hover { border-color: var(--ink-blue); }
    .related-label {
        display: block; font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 10px;
        letter-spacing: 0.14em; text-transform: uppercase; color: var(--ink-3);
        margin-bottom: 4px;
    }
    .related-card strong { font-size: 15px; }

    @media (max-width: 768px) {
        .story-hero h1 { font-size: 2.2rem; }
        .map-section { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
        .map-divider {
            writing-mode: horizontal-tb; border: none;
            border-top: 1px dashed var(--rule); border-bottom: 1px dashed var(--rule);
            padding: 8px 0;
        }
        .related-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
    }
</style>
